abstract: Members of Congress said they would look into antitrust issues raised by Comcast’s planned acquisition of Time Warner Cable.
snippet: Members of Congress said they would look into antitrust issues raised by Comcast’s planned acquisition of Time Warner Cable.
lead_paragraph: The ink on Comcast’s $45.2 billion agreement to acquire Time Warner Cable is barely dry, but already lawmakers have begun to weigh in on the antitrust issues raised by the deal, the largest this year so far.

headline_main: Lawmakers Promise Scrutiny of Comcast Deal

abstract: Comcast’s proposed acquisition of Time Warner Cable will face extensive scrutiny.
snippet: Comcast’s proposed acquisition of Time Warner Cable will face extensive scrutiny.
lead_paragraph: On the face of it, the merger of the country’s two largest cable companies would seem like a nonstarter, given its steep regulatory hurdles and skepticism from consumer watchdogs.

snippet: As cars increasingly come equipped with Internet connections, GPS and data recorders, concerns about what is being tracked and who has access to it.
lead_paragraph: Cars are becoming smarter than ever, with global positioning systems, Internet connections, data recorders and high-definition cameras. Drivers can barely make a left turn, put on their seatbelts or push 80 miles an hour without their actions somehow, somewhere being tracked or recorded.

abstract: Senator Harry Reid has engaged in the greatest consolidation of congressional power since Newt Gingrich led the House, unleashing a bitterness that may derail efforts to extend unemployment insurance.
snippet: Senator Harry Reid has engaged in the greatest consolidation of congressional power since Newt Gingrich led the House, unleashing a bitterness that may derail efforts to extend unemployment insurance.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — With his strong-armed change to the filibuster rule and an iron-fisted control of the Senate floor, Senator Harry Reid has engaged in the greatest consolidation of congressional power since Newt Gingrich ruled the House, unleashing a bitterness that may derail efforts to extend unemployment insurance.

headline_main: Reid’s Uncompromising Power Play in Senate Rankles Republicans
headline_print_headline: Reid’s Uncompromising Power Play in Senate Rankles Republicans

abstract: The bipartisan budget deal may not be a cure-all for the gridlock in Washington, but it provides a much-needed break in the inaction.
snippet: The bipartisan budget deal may not be a cure-all for the gridlock in Washington, but it provides a much-needed break in the inaction.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Something odd happened here on Tuesday. The Senate advanced a two-year bipartisan budget deal that will now surely be sent to the president for his signature later this week without waiting for a cliff, a chasm, a deadline or a shutdown to force its hand.
